	 <p id="caption_title_battery">BATTERY</p>
	  <%=image_tag "2.1.jpg", id: "default" %>
	   <p id="caption_definition">Any “uncontested to touching” causing harm to any part of the body.
		If you consent to the harm, then it will not be battery.</p>
	   <p id="caption_story">“Angry Earl hits Andy for forgetting to pay him back forty dollars. (BATTERY) Andy, betting Angry Earl forty dollars that he is invincible, dares Earl to hit him. (NOT BATTERY)</p>
	  </div>
	</div>

	<div class="w3-display-container mySlides1 fade">
	<div class="numbertext1">2 / 3</div>
	<p id="caption_title_assault">ASSAULT</p>
	 <%=image_tag "2.2.jpg", id: "default" %>
	    <p id="caption_definition">Intent to create a reasonable apprehension of an imminent bodily injury that is likely to result in a harmful contact.<br> A.􏰀 There doesn’t have to be actual physical contact.<br> B.􏰀 Victim must be aware of the assault. <br> C.􏰀 If victim laughs, then it is not assault.</p>
	   <p id="caption_story">“Angry Earl chases a frightened Andy with a baseball bat. (ASSAULT). Angry Earl chases Andy who is laughing, not taking him seriously. (NOT ASSAULT)"</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="w3-display-container mySlides1 fade">
	<div class="numbertext1">3 / 3</div>
	    <p id="caption_title_transferred_intent">TRANSFERRED INTENT</p>
	      <%=image_tag "2.3.jpg", id: "default" %>
	    <p id="caption_definition">You accidentally inflict harm to another person when you intended to do so to someone else. Regardless, you are still liable.</p>
	   <p id="caption_story">“On the dance floor, a man taunts Andy’s weak frame. Unable to control his anger at that moment, Andy attempts to punch the man. Except, he ducks, and Andy accidentally hits Burly Joe."</p>
	  </div>
